  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b85\u0bb0\u0b9a\u0bbe\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b87\u0bae\u0bcd\u0bae\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bc8 \u0b9c\u0bc6\u0ba9\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baf \u0ba8\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0b9f\u0bbf \u0b8f\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd - \u0baa\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b9c\u0bbf.\u0b8e\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bc0\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0bb8\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The Government will face a massive crisis this time in Geneva - Professor GL Peiris",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "Emergency law, violations of democratic rights will be given special attention during the 51st session of the United Nations Human Rights Council. Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna is currently acting contrary to the policy and the constitution of the party, said Prof. GL Peiris, Deputy Director of Podujana Peramuna.",
        "He mentioned the above while attending a press conference in Colombo yesterday.",
        "I voted against the Emergency because it would affect the fundamental rights of the people of the country. There is no need to implement emergency law in the current state. Emergency law will call into question human rights.",
        "The Emergency Act has been imposed against the policy of the Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna and against the party's constitution. Podujana Peramuna is currently acting in an unprincipled manner. Activities contrary to the policy of the party are currently being carried out.",
        "If emergency laws are imposed to suppress democratic people's struggle, the result will be adverse. Emergency law can call into question all other laws except the Constitution. Emergency law also affects human rights.",
        "The international community has paid special attention to Sri Lanka due to the implementation of the emergency law while expecting international assistance while facing a severe economic crisis. All over the world countries and human rights organizations have expressed their strong condemnation of the brutal attack on the empty-faced protestors.",
        "Sri Lanka will definitely face huge challenges during the 51st session of the United Nations Human Rights Council in September. GSP's anti-democratic activities. He said that the provision of plus tax credit has been taken to the point of cancellation."
      ],
